This paper deals with a communication system with a single server, which is a common topic in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the age of information metric, which is a measure of the freshness of information in a system, and this is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers two service discipline models, which are related to control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses stochastic ordering, which is a mathematical concept that is often used in probability theory and statistics (cs.PF). Finally, the paper derives upper bounds using mathematical techniques, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
